node.text: Short film by @taylorglenn | We all know people whose dedication to a passion or purpose inspires us deeply. Gannett Horn's (@surfasaur) focus on his sport and love for its community embodies the best in each of us. This short film is a testament to Gannett and those who motivate us to work harder at the things we love. #riversurfing Production by @apresvisuals

node.text: Photo by Chris Boyes @christurtleboyes / Sunset over Mambatuta Falls of the Luapula River, waters of the Congo! Exploring the Congo Basin area of northern Zambia. The Luapula is such an integral part of this water’s story, draining out of the Bangweulu Swamps System, rushing its way to Lake Mweru, forming the border of the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Zambia, with tributaries stretching deep into both countries, it is a binding river.
